article_title: Kim Strassel: How Coburn Made a Difference
article_text:
Members of Congress come and go, and many leave Washington no better or worse than they found it. A few make a mark, and Congress is losing one of them: Tom Coburn.

The senator doesn’t leave behind him a stack of legislation with his name, or grand bipartisan deals. He doesn’t leave stunts, public tantrums, an adoring press corps, or, for that matter, many adoring GOP colleagues. Mr. Coburn didn’t really “do” legacy. Which is why...

article_metadata.author: Kimberley A. Strassel

article_summary:
He doesn’t leave stunts, public tantrums, an adoring press corps, or, for that matter, many adoring GOP colleagues.
Members of Congress come and go, and many leave Washington no better or worse than they found it.
The senator doesn’t leave behind him a stack of legislation with his name, or grand bipartisan deals.
A few make a mark, and Congress is losing one of them: Tom Coburn.
Mr. Coburn didn’t really “do” legacy.
